## Overview 

Now that we have Packet Tracer Installed, it's time to go over the basics. 

## User Interface 

- Under the "file" bar, there are your typical "New", "Open", "Save", and "Save As" options avaiailable. 
  However, there is also an "Open Samples" option. Under this, there are pre-existing device and protocol 
  examples that you can explore. 
- Options -> Preferences 
    - Under the interface tab, you can customize the user's experience
    - Under "Font" you can adjust the font size and colors
    - Under "Miscellaneous", there is an "Auto File Backup Interval" option that you can turn on, although 
      it is off by default
- Logical
    - Illustrates how devices are connected and how data will flow through the network.
- Physical
    - Illustrates how the devices are laid out and connected.
-Realtime 
    - The real time in the network as things are happening
- Simulation
    - Allows you to control the time as well as add packets and watch them travel across the network
- Scenario Box
    - Here we can create packets on the network to travel across multiple devices and to be able to see those 
      packets as they travel across the network.


## Deploying Devices

